- No.

261
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:08,997
No, I'm afraid we're a travel bookshop.
We only sell travel books.

262
00:18:10,557 --> 00:18:13,677
Oh, right. How about
the new John Grisham thriller?

263
00:18:15,077 --> 00:18:18,917
Well, no, 'cause that's, uh--
that's a novel too, isn't it?

264
00:18:18,997 --> 00:18:21,677
Oh, right.

265
00:18:22,837 --> 00:18:27,877
[ Sighs ]
Have you got Winnie the Pooh?

266
00:18:29,397 --> 00:18:31,758
Martin, your customer.

267
00:18:31,798 --> 00:18:33,798
- Uh, can I help you?
- [ Bell Dinging ]

268
00:18:36,558 --> 00:18:40,118
% [ Pop ]

269
00:18:40,198 --> 00:18:42,478
% Once in a lifetime %

270
00:18:44,758 --> 00:18:46,638
- % [ Continues ]
- Hey.

271
00:18:46,678 --> 00:18:48,558
Hi.

272
00:18:50,038 --> 00:18:54,598
- % Once in a lifetime %
- Just, um, incidentally,

273
00:18:54,678 --> 00:18:57,518
uh, why...
are you wearing that?

274
00:18:57,598 --> 00:19:01,199
Combination of factors really.
Uh, no clean clothes.

275
00:19:01,239 --> 00:19:04,999
There never will be, you know,
unless you actually clean your clothes.

276
00:19:05,079 --> 00:19:07,399
Right.
Vicious circle.

277
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:10,039
And I was, like,
rooting around in your things...

278
00:19:10,119 --> 00:19:12,039
and I found this,
and I thought "cool".

279
00:19:13,639 --> 00:19:16,119
Kinda... spacey.

280
00:19:19,119 --> 00:19:21,919
There's something wrong
with the goggles, though.

281
00:19:21,959 --> 00:19:24,759
No, they were, um, prescription.

282
00:19:24,839 --> 00:19:28,320
- Groovy.
- So I could see all the fishes properly.

283
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,880
You should do more
of this stuff.

284
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:34,760
- So, look, any messages today?
- Yeah, I wrote a couple down.

285
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:38,080
So there were two.
There were two messages? Right?

286
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:43,160
You want me to write down
all your messages?

287
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:47,200
Okay, who are the ones
that you didn't write down from?

288
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,960
[ Sighs ]

289
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,400
No. Gone completely.

290
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,320
Oh, no.
There was one from your mum.

291
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:54,880
She said don't forget lunch,
and her leg's hurting again.

292
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,441
- No one else?
- Absolutely no one else.

293
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:03,881
Though if we're going for this obsessive
writing down all the message thing,

294
00:20:03,961 --> 00:20:07,241
some American girl called Anna
called a few days ago.

295
00:20:12,561 --> 00:20:15,401
- What did she say?
- Well, it was genuinely bizarre.

296
00:20:15,441 --> 00:20:20,681
She said, "Hi. It's Anna."
