297
00:20:20,761 --> 00:20:24,121
and then gave herself
a completely different name.

298
00:20:24,201 --> 00:20:27,962
- Which was?
- Absolutely no idea.

299
00:20:28,042 --> 00:20:30,362
Remembering one name's hard enough.

300
00:20:30,442 --> 00:20:32,602
No, I-- I know that.
She-- She said that.

301
00:20:32,682 --> 00:20:34,842
Um, I know she's using another name.

302
00:20:34,922 --> 00:20:38,202
The problem is
she left the message with my flatmate...

303
00:20:38,282 --> 00:20:40,162
which was a very serious mistake.

304
00:20:40,202 --> 00:20:44,322
Um, I don't know. Imagine, if you will,
the stupidest person you've ever met.

305
00:20:44,402 --> 00:20:48,482
- Are you doing that?
- Yes, sir, I have him in my mind.

306
00:20:48,522 --> 00:20:51,682
And now double it.
And that is the, um-- what can I say--

307
00:20:51,762 --> 00:20:54,243
the git that I am living with.

308
00:20:54,283 --> 00:20:55,643
And he can't remember--

309
00:20:55,723 --> 00:20:58,683
- Try Flintstone.
- I'm sorry, what?

310
00:20:58,763 --> 00:21:02,043
I think she said
her name was Flintstone.

311
00:21:04,043 --> 00:21:08,763
I don't-- I don't suppose, um,
Flintstone rings any bells, does it?

312
00:21:08,843 --> 00:21:12,003
- Oh, I'll put you right through, sir.
- Oh, my God.

313
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:17,563
Hello. Hi.

314
00:21:17,643 --> 00:21:19,483
- Hi there.
- Hello?

315
00:21:19,563 --> 00:21:21,403
Hi. Hi.

316
00:21:21,483 --> 00:21:25,084
- Sorry. It's William... Thacker.
- Yes?

317
00:21:25,164 --> 00:21:27,564
Um, we-- I work in a bookshop.

318
00:21:27,644 --> 00:21:31,364
Uh-huh. You played it pretty cool there,
waiting for three days to call.

319
00:21:31,404 --> 00:21:34,524
Oh, no, I promise you I've never played
anything cool in my entire life.

320
00:21:34,604 --> 00:21:37,924
My flatmate, who'll I'll stab to death
later, never gave me the message.

321
00:21:39,444 --> 00:21:42,004
I don't know.
Perhaps, um,

322
00:21:42,084 --> 00:21:46,244
I could drop round
for tea later or something.

323
00:21:46,284 --> 00:21:51,085
- Things are pretty busy here.
I might be free around 4:00.
- Right. Right. Great.

324
00:21:51,165 --> 00:21:53,765
- Bye.
- Yea-- Bye.

325
00:21:53,845 --> 00:21:56,325
[ Phone Clicks, Dial Tone ]

326
00:21:59,245 --> 00:22:01,085
Classic.

327
00:22:05,805 --> 00:22:07,645
Classic.

328
00:22:32,246 --> 00:22:35,086
% [ Piano ]

329
00:22:35,126 --> 00:22:37,966
% [ Continues ]

