00:22:44,046 --> 00:22:46,566
- Which floor?
- Three, please.

331
00:22:52,447 --> 00:22:54,287
[ Elevator Dings ]

332
00:23:13,847 --> 00:23:16,487
Uh, are you sure this is--

333
00:23:16,527 --> 00:23:19,128
Oh, yeah. Yeah. Sure.

334
00:23:29,968 --> 00:23:31,808
- Hi. Hi. I'm Karen.
- Hi.

335
00:23:31,888 --> 00:23:34,288
I'm sorry.
Things are running a little bit late.

336
00:23:34,368 --> 00:23:38,288
Here's the, uh, thing.
Do you wanna come this way?

337
00:23:38,368 --> 00:23:40,968
[ Karen ]
Through here.

338
00:23:41,048 --> 00:23:44,848
[ Reporters Chattering ]

339
00:23:44,888 --> 00:23:47,249
So what did you
think of the film?

340
00:23:47,289 --> 00:23:49,969
Yeah, I thought it was fantastic.
I thought it was, uh,

341
00:23:50,049 --> 00:23:53,449
Close Encounters
meets Jean de Florette.

342
00:23:55,449 --> 00:23:57,329
I agree.

343
00:23:57,369 --> 00:24:00,209
I'm sorry. I didn't get down
what magazines you're from.

344
00:24:00,249 --> 00:24:02,649
- Time Out.
- Great.

345
00:24:02,729 --> 00:24:05,569
And you're from?

346
00:24:08,369 --> 00:24:12,289
Uh, Horse & Hound.

347
00:24:16,530 --> 00:24:20,010
The name's William Thacker. I think,
actually, she might be expecting me.

348
00:24:20,050 --> 00:24:22,730
Oh, okay.
Take a seat and I'll go check.

349
00:24:26,170 --> 00:24:29,450
I see you've, uh--
I see you've brought her some flowers.

350
00:24:29,490 --> 00:24:32,330
[ Laughing ]
No.

351
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:35,570
These are for my,
um, grandmother.

352
00:24:35,650 --> 00:24:38,290
She's in a hospital
just down the road.

353
00:24:38,370 --> 00:24:40,970
Thought I'd kill two birds
with one stone, you know.

354
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:44,171
Sure, right.
Absolutely. Yeah. Yeah.

355
00:24:44,251 --> 00:24:46,891
Which hospital's that?

356
00:24:46,931 --> 00:24:48,971
Do you mind me not saying?

357
00:24:49,051 --> 00:24:51,211
It's a rather distressing disease.

358
00:24:51,291 --> 00:24:53,931
- Name of the hospital
kind of gives it away.
- Absolutely. Sure.

359
00:24:53,971 --> 00:24:55,851
Cheers.
Ooh, yes.

360
00:24:55,891 --> 00:24:58,571
Right, uh, Mr. Thacker.
Will you come this way.

361
00:24:58,651 --> 00:25:00,971
Right.

362
00:25:01,011 --> 00:25:03,771
You've got five minutes.

363
00:25:12,212 --> 00:25:15,252
- Hi.
- Hello.

364
00:25:15,332 --> 00:25:19,132
Uh, I brought these, but clearly--

365
00:25:19,212 --> 00:25:22,852
No, they're great.
They're great.

366
00:25:22,932 --> 00:25:25,652
Ah, listen,
I'm sorry about not ringing back.

367
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:27,572
The whole "two-names concept"...

368
00:25:27,652 --> 00:25:30,052
was totally too much for my flatmate's
pea-sized intellect.

369
00:25:30,132 --> 00:25:33,812
No, it's a stupid privacy thing.
I always pick a... cartoon character.

370
00:25:33,892 --> 00:25:36,012
Last time I was Mrs. Bambi.

371
00:25:36,052 --> 00:25:38,732
[ Door Closes ]

372
00:25:38,772 --> 00:25:41,893
- Everything all right?
- Yes, thank you.

373
00:25:41,973 --> 00:25:44,653
And you're from, uh,
Horse & Hound.

374
00:25:44,693 --> 00:25:47,213
- Yeah.
- Good.

375
00:25:47,253 --> 00:25:49,893
Is that so? Well.

376
00:25:55,613 --> 00:25:57,653
So, uh--

377
00:26:00,653 --> 00:26:05,653
Uh, I'll just... fire away then,
shall I?

378
00:26:07,173 --> 00:26:09,134
Right.

379
00:26:09,214 --> 00:26:11,094
Uh--

380
00:26:12,454 --> 00:26:15,654
The film's great, and, um,

381
00:26:15,734 --> 00:26:18,574
I just was wondering whether...

382
00:26:18,654 --> 00:26:20,734
you ever thought of having, um,

383
00:26:20,814 --> 00:26:24,374
more, uh, horses in it.

384
00:26:24,454 --> 00:26:27,334
[ Clears Throat ]

385
00:26:27,414 --> 00:26:30,774
Uh, well, we would have liked to,

386
00:26:30,854 --> 00:26:35,974
but it was, um, difficult,
obviously, being set in space.

387
00:26:37,415 --> 00:26:41,095
Space, right, yeah.
Yeah, obviously very difficult.

388
00:26:42,455 --> 00:26:44,295
I'm so sorry.
I arrived outside.

389
00:26:44,375 --> 00:26:46,255
They thrust this thing
into my hand--

390
00:26:46,295 --> 00:26:49,455
No, it's my fault.
I thought this would all be over by now.

391
00:26:49,535 --> 00:26:52,175
I just wanted to sort of apologize
for the kissing thing.

392
00:26:52,215 --> 00:26:54,095
I seriously don't know
what came over me.

393
00:26:54,135 --> 00:26:57,015
And I just wanted to make sure
that you were fine about it.

394
00:26:58,775 --> 00:27:04,015
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Absolutely fine.
- [ Door Closes ]

395
00:27:04,095 --> 00:27:08,096
Do remember that Miss Scott is also
keen to talk about her next project...

396
00:27:08,176 --> 00:27:11,696
which is, um, shooting
later in the summer.

397
00:27:11,776 --> 00:27:15,096
Ah, yes, excellent.
Excellent.

398
00:27:19,896 --> 00:27:23,856
Any horses in that one?

399
00:27:23,896 --> 00:27:29,136
Or hounds for that matter. Our readers
are equally intrigued by both species.

400
00:27:29,176 --> 00:27:31,856
It takes place on a submarine.

401
00:27:31,936 --> 00:27:35,257
Oh. Well, bad luck.

402
00:27:36,617 --> 00:27:39,137
But, um,

403
00:27:39,217 --> 00:27:41,417
if there were horses in it,

404
00:27:41,497 --> 00:27:43,977
would you be riding them...

405
00:27:44,057 --> 00:27:48,497
or would you be getting, a--
a stunt-horse-double-man-thing?

406
00:27:50,777 --> 00:27:55,417
[ Chuckles ] I-- I'm a complete moron.
I apologize. I--

407
00:27:55,497 --> 00:27:59,257
This is very weird. It's the sort
of thing that happens in dreams,

408
00:27:59,297 --> 00:28:01,777
not in real life.

409
00:28:01,857 --> 00:28:04,258
I mean, good dreams.
It's a--

410
00:28:04,338 --> 00:28:07,738
it's a dream, in fact,
uh, to see you again.

411
00:28:09,258 --> 00:28:12,778
What happens next in the dream?

412
00:28:14,578 --> 00:28:18,778
I suppose in the, uh, dream--

413
00:28:18,818 --> 00:28:22,258
dream scenario--
I just, uh,

414
00:28:22,298 --> 00:28:24,418
change my personality...

415
00:28:24,498 --> 00:28:27,018
because you can do that
in dreams and, um,

416
00:28:29,298 --> 00:28:33,379
walk over and, uh, kiss the girl.

417
00:28:33,459 --> 00:28:35,979
But, uh--

418
00:28:43,339 --> 00:28:46,899
Time's up, I'm afraid.
Did you get what you wanted?

419
00:28:46,979 --> 00:28:51,979
- Um, nearly, nearly.
- Well, maybe just one last question.

420
00:28:53,299 --> 00:28:55,819
- Sure. [ Clears Throat ]
- Right, right.

421
00:28:57,419 --> 00:28:59,260
[ Door Closes ]

422
00:28:59,340 --> 00:29:02,580
Are you... busy tonight?

423
00:29:02,660 --> 00:29:07,340
- Yes.
- Right. Right.

424
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:12,660
- Come in.
- Well, it was nice to meet you.

425
00:29:12,740 --> 00:29:14,900
Yes, and you.

426
00:29:14,980 --> 00:29:17,300
Surreal... but nice.

427
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:21,580
Thank you. You are Horse & Hounds'
favorite actress.

428
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:25,260
You and Black Beauty...

429
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:27,180
tied.

430
00:29:32,101 --> 00:29:33,941
How was she?

431
00:29:34,021 --> 00:29:37,381
Oh, um, fabulous.

432
00:29:37,421 --> 00:29:41,381
Excellent. Wait a minute.
She took your grandmother's flowers.

433
00:29:41,421 --> 00:29:44,861
Uh, yeah, yeah.
That's right.

434
00:29:44,941 --> 00:29:46,901
- Bitch.
- [ Karen ] Oh, Mr. Thacker.

435
00:29:46,981 --> 00:29:51,221
Mr. Thacker, if you'd like to come with
me, we can rush you through the others.

436
00:29:51,301 --> 00:29:52,661
The others?

437
00:29:52,741 --> 00:29:55,221
Mr. Thacker is from Horse & Hound.

438
00:29:58,062 --> 00:30:00,662
- How's it going?
- Very well, thank you.

439
00:30:00,742 --> 00:30:03,822
Have a seat.

440
00:30:03,862 --> 00:30:06,942
